ient way to make money at the early levels?  I'd assume it would be making those stacks of batwings to sell for a couple of plat, but is there another?  I saw someone mention baking as a viable source of income, but I could have misread.  Getting a good piercer won't exactly be easy, but I'm willing to invest time and energy with tradeskills or on quests in order to afford one.  I like the &quot;journey over destination&quot; comments I've been reading about, and am quite looking forward to this. Eventually, I'd like for Ravero to join a guild, but I leave that in the hands of good roleplay and a little bit of fate.   ;-)<br><br>Any info would be appreciated!<br><br>--------------------------------------------------<br><br>Ravero's player, Vlad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaze9999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaze9999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 1:25:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> Seems like the barbarian rogue quests (even if you are a half-elf) offer the best starting rogue equipment that you can earn through quests.  This server is harder then most to earn cash on, and my opinion, no trade skill will even cover its own costs for quite a while, much less make you a profit.<br><br>And maybe you meant this, but half elves CAN have facial hair. Just no ability to pick color or style. Only the one choice. <p>Proverbs 27 Wounds from a friend can be trusted, but an enemy multiplies kisses.<BR>  Ecclesiastes 4 If one falls down, his friend can help him up. But pity the man who falls and has no one to help him up!<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 1:28:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> If you check the market forums below, you will notice that there are almost always people buying spiderling silk, spider silk, various pelts, and bone chips... if you aren't planning to be a tradesperson, hunting those things seems a comfortable way to make some spare plat on the side.<br><br>There is also a secondary market in TLC-affected loot for various quests. It seems rather erratic, and tied to being in the right place with the right factions and levels at the right time, but it can be an option if you make it known you will quest for others.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Terror of spiderkin all over Faydwer, but for my own purposes... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uqilanifv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QilaniFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 1:30:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> Kills animals.  Save the pelts... all pelts.  I see people looking for all grades of pelts rather often.<br><br>Kill spiders and stack those silks.  People look for them rather often.<br><br>Kill skeletons and save those bone chips.  You see people paying upward to 5pp a stack for them.<br><br>If it has a weapon, kill it.  Some go upwards of two gold. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Basically... scrounge.  Scrounge.  Scrounge some more.<br><br>It's tough.  I went through it myself recently.  Made the jump to Vie from my two established servers, and Qil, Vel, and Vell all had to learn how to survive on scraps instead of my usual twink packages.<br><br>It's not as hard as it sounds and it actually can be quite fun (specially when you are a caster have enough for one new spell circle spell, but have two you could really use =/ lol) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeffhead01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffhead01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnevil Mastermind</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 1:31:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.coolwebsites.dk/lasse/lasse_2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> Money early on...Well, I'd say the Warrens. Excellent loot, lots of prey, and usually quite alot of people so it shouldn't be too hard for you get a partner or group.<br>It depends a little on who/what you are ofcourse, since some races/classes will have a very hard time getting there.<br>Apart from that, I'd say look for low level TLC items that are used in higher level quests, like those Ghasts hearts from Lesser Faydark...Else you can never go wrong with Will-o-whisps<br><br><br>/Rokkhead Deffstomp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uforgehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forgehammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wacking Warrior<br>Baking Barbarian</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 1:49:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> Warrens is the place to go. Easy money. Lots of the wepaons sell for one or two platinum each to the vendors.<br><br><br>Can't go wrong there.<br><br>Lasonta (now 50% brighter with Greater Lightstone)<br>Barbarian warrior vacationing in beautiful Freeport.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 2:06:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To all the money-makers...</span><hr size=1> Oh, yeah... forgot about the 'pathetic wimp critters with weapons' thing! If you see an orc/skeleton/goblin with a staff, KILL IT! Half the time it will be a cracked staff, and those sell back to vendors for nearly a plat! Other weapons (rusty swords and spears and axes) are nice, but cracked staves are like winning the newbie lottery.<br><br>My only hunting experience is Faydwer, but orcs (cloth armor and weapons), wolves and pumas (pelts), skeletons (weapons, cloth armor, and bone chips) spiders and spiderlings (silk and venom), and wasps (venom and royal jelly) all have a chance of dropping stuff that sells well to either merchants or players - and make good newbie hunting.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Connoisseur of Crap Loot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lest>Lest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 2:37:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> definitely hunt crap loot</span><hr size=1> Everything I own was purchased through rusty weapons, cloth armor and newbie quest items. I did the orc hatchet quest in Kelethin and bone chip and crushbone belt quests intensely at baby levels not only for experience, but because the weapons/armor awarded were more often than not worth more than a gold to a vendor. <br><br>Now I'm just starting the great willowisp hunt, like so many before me...<br><br>Lest<br>frugal ranger extraordinaire<br>You have become better at penny-pinching (3)! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showPrevMessage?topicID=44.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showNextMessage?topicID=44.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=